Grey seals have been spied feasting on harbour porpoises off the coast of Pembrokeshire on four separate occasions . 
  This is the first time they have been spotted in Britain . 
  The footage was shot by a wildlife cruise company and backs up a recent study that they attack healthy creatures . 
  Killer seals are known to lurk in the waters off the continent . 
  Scientists said the seals may have a taste for porpoise caught in fishing nets and warned people could be next . 
 